CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 12, 1966, pg. 4B reads: "The Rangerettes -Elk dignitaries from many places were on hand to help the Rangerettes of Western Pennsylvania celebrate their 15th anniversary recently.  Seated: Elizabeth Madden, honoree; Hester R. Thomas, State President; Nettie B. Smith, Grand Daughter Ruler of New York City; Clara Randolph, Deputy, and Alice Wilkerson, Captain.  Standing: Past Captain, Edmonia Harrington, Bessie Woods, Beatrice Dickey, James Madden, husband of honoree; Dorothy Lowery, Past Captain; Claire Smith, co-chairman; Alice Crisp, William Long, Davis Kirk, Georgia Robinson, Sarah Norton, Florence Johnson and Mabel Meek. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Elks and Rangerettes members, including: Elizabeth Madden, honoree; Hester R. Thomas, Nettie B. Smith, Clara Randolph, and Alice Wilkerson; standing: Edmonia Harington, Bessie Woods, Beatrice Dickey, James Madden, Dorothy Lowery, Claire Smith, Alice Crisp, William Long, Davis Kirk, Georgia Robinson, Sarah Norton, Florence Johnson, and Mabel Meek, gathered in North Side Elks lodge for Rangerettes fifteenth anniversary party
